Date: 0/0/1966
Source: English Language in Aust. & NZ, The
Author: TURNER
Vol / Page: 163
Edition:
Quote: There are several local names for winds, the <i>doctor</i> in Perth, ... the <i>barber</i> in Greymouth, N Z, a very cutting wind, the Canterbury <i>nor'wester</i> resembling the European<i> Fohn</i> wind, ... and the <i>three-day sou'wester</i> in New Zealand, a form of the <i>southerly buster</i>, a name used in both Australia and New Zealand, probably more often in the shortened form a [sic] <i>southerly. </i>
